excerpt: Tour the historic royal castle full of spectacular art & antiques, plus grounds & a chapel.
detail_description: Windsor Castle, located in the royal borough of Windsor, is the oldest and largest inhabited castle globally. It has served as the family home for British monarchs for nearly a millennium and is currently an official residence of Her Majesty The Queen. The castle features spectacular art, antiques, and a chapel within its grounds.
name: Windsor Castle
address: Windsor, SL4 1NJ, United Kingdom

excerpt: Playful property with thrill rides, Lego statues & themed rooms, plus free Wi-Fi & breakfast.
detail_description: LEGOLAND® Windsor Resort is a playful property that offers thrill rides, Lego statues, and themed rooms. It also provides free Wi-Fi and breakfast for guests. While in the area, visitors can explore the town and surrounding areas on an all-day hop-on, hop-off bus tour that includes stops at various points of interest such as Windsor Great Park, Eton College, Datchet Green for river cruises, and The Long Walk.
name: LEGOLAND® Windsor Resort
address: Winkfield Rd, Windsor, SL4 4AY, United Kingdom

excerpt: Ornate, 14th-century place of royal worship with cloisters and links to ancient chivalric orders.
detail_description: St George's Chapel, located within the grounds of Windsor Castle, is a stunning example of late medieval Perpendicular Gothic architecture. Founded in the 14th century by King Edward III and expanded in the late 15th century, it has been an integral part of royal history for centuries. As a place of worship, it hosts multiple services daily and is open to visitors, except on Sundays.
name: St George's Chapel
address: Castle, Windsor, SL4 1NJ, United Kingdom

excerpt: Iconic Tudor-era boarding school with Gothic chapel, whose former pupils include 19 prime ministers.
detail_description: Eton College is an iconic Tudor-era boarding school with a Gothic chapel, boasting a prestigious legacy of British education. Established in 1440, it has produced some of the world's brightest minds, including notable alumni such as Prince William and Prime Minister David Cameron. The annual Windsor Festival offers a variety of cultural events at venues like the Waterloo Chamber and Eton College Chapel.
name: Eton College
address: Windsor, SL4 6DW, United Kingdom

excerpt: A diverse range of shows from live music acts to dramatic theatre, plus a Picturehouse cinema.
detail_description: The Theatre Royal Windsor, located just a stone's throw from the grand Windsor Castle, offers a diverse range of shows including live music acts, dramatic theater performances, and screenings at its Picturehouse cinema. The theater itself has a rich 200-year-old history dating back to the time of King George II and features opulent decor with lush red velvet seats, high ceilings, and a vast crystal chandelier.
name: Theatre Royal Windsor
address: 32 Thames St, Windsor, SL4 1PS, United Kingdom

excerpt: Windsor is a town on the River Thames in southeast England, just west of London. It’s home to Windsor Castle, a residence of the British Royal Family. Built by William The Conqueror in the 11th century, the castle was extensively remodelled by subsequent monarchs. Public tours take in the State Apartments, which contain opulent furnishings, and paintings from the royal art collection.
detail_description: Windsor, located in southeast England near London, is renowned for its historic Windsor Castle, a residence of the British Royal Family. The castle, originally built by William The Conqueror in the 11th century and later renovated by successive monarchs, offers public tours of its opulent State Apartments and royal art collection.
name: Windsor
address: UK

excerpt: Racing over a figure-of-eight flat course, plus afternoon teas, conferences and events.
detail_description: Royal Windsor Racecourse, situated in Windsor, Berkshire, is a renowned venue with over 150 years of history. It offers thrilling horse racing events on a figure-of-eight flat course and is frequented by the royal family. The racecourse hosts various meetings throughout the season, providing a lively atmosphere for spectators amidst picturesque views along the River Thames. Additionally, visitors can enjoy afternoon teas, conferences, and events at this charming location.
name: Royal Windsor Racecourse
address: Maidenhead Rd, Windsor, SL4 5JJ, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Windsor & Royal Borough Museum, located in the historic Windsor Guildhall, offers a family-friendly exploration of East Berkshire's rich history. Visitors can immerse themselves in interactive displays and audio trails featuring local residents' stories about Windsor's evolving landscape. The museum boasts a diverse collection, including a 100,000-year-old Mammoth tusk and a model of the Hawker Hurricane designed by Windsor-born Sir Sydney Camm.
name: Windsor & Royal Borough Museum
address: & Royal Borough Museum, 51 High St, Windsor SL4 1LR, United Kingdom

detail_description: Windsor Guildhall, serving as the Town Hall of Windsor, is a historic venue that has hosted numerous charity fundraisers, dinner events, and weddings of famous couples. Notably, Prince Charles and Camilla had their civil wedding ceremony here in 2005. The elegant building was partly constructed by Sir Christopher Wren and features a covered area beneath supported by stone columns.
name: Windsor Guildhall
address: 51 High St, Windsor, SL4 1LR, United Kingdom

excerpt: Owned by the Crown Estate, this 17th-century English country house offers seasonal guided tours.
detail_description: Frogmore House and Gardens, a 17th-century royal residence nestled within Windsor Home Park, is a must-visit for history and nature enthusiasts, as well as royal watchers. The estate offers seasonal guided tours of its elegant interiors showcasing art and royal memorabilia. Visitors can also explore the beautifully landscaped gardens featuring various plants, flowers, and tranquil spots.
name: Frogmore House and Gardens
address: Home Park, Frogmore Dr, Windsor, SL4 2JG, United Kingdom

excerpt: English tea room serving breakfast, lunch and afternoon tea in a wonky 16th-century timbered house.
detail_description: The Crooked House of Windsor is a charming 16th-century timbered house that has become a popular attraction in Windsor. Rebuilt in haste in 1687, the building's wooden frame buckled as it dried, resulting in its unique and quirky crooked structure that still stands today. This historic landmark has served various purposes over the years, including being a butchers, jewelers, and brewery.
name: The Crooked House of Windsor
address: 51 High St, Windsor, SL4 1LR, United Kingdom

excerpt: Eton is a town in Berkshire, England, on the opposite bank of the River Thames to Windsor, connected to it by Windsor Bridge. The civil parish, which also includes the village of Eton Wick two miles west of the town, had a population of 4,692 at the 2011 census. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Eton, located in Berkshire, England, sits on the opposite side of the River Thames from Windsor and is linked to it by Windsor Bridge. The town, along with the village of Eton Wick, has a combined population of 4,692 as per the 2011 Census. Eton offers a charming selection of coffee shops such as Arte Food and Nimia in addition to eateries like Heidi Bakery and Craft Coffee House.
name: Eton
address: Windsor, UK

detail_description: Located on the high street, Windsor Parish Church of St John the Baptist has a rich history dating back to the 12th century. The current church was consecrated in 1822 after the previous Norman building was demolished due to extensive repair costs. Many monuments from the old church were relocated to the new one, including stone memorials dating back to the 16th and 17th centuries.
name: Windsor Parish Church of St John the Baptist
address: High St, Windsor, SL4 1LS, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Long Walk is a famous 2.64-mile avenue that runs from the gates of Windsor Castle to the statue of King George III, known as The Copper Horse, on Snow Hill in Windsor Great Park. This straight walkway offers stunning views of the castle and even extends to London's skyline on clear days. It's a popular spot for visitors and locals alike, offering a picturesque stroll through Windsor Great Park.
name: The Long Walk
address: The Long Walk Rd, Windsor, SL4 2JG, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Dr Choc's Windsor Chocolate Factory is a delightful place with friendly staff and excellent chocolate. You can join a chocolate workshop and make your own chocolate. The waffles are especially good here!
name: Dr Choc's Windsor Chocolate Factory
address: 23 Thames St, Windsor, SL4 1PL, United Kingdom

detail_description: If you're looking for a unique experience in Windsor, the Windsor & Eton Brewery is a must-visit destination. This charming craft brewery, established in 2010, invites you to explore its artisanal brewing techniques while enjoying a tasting session of their exceptional ales. The taproom features an impressive selection of over 20 beers on tap at any given time, including delightful options like Guardsman Best Bitter and Knight of the Garter Golden Ale.
name: Windsor & Eton Brewery
address: 1-4 Vansittart Estate, Duke St, Windsor SL4 1SE, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Long Walk Rd is a picturesque route that offers stunning views of the surrounding landscape. It's a great place for leisurely strolls, with well-maintained paths and plenty of natural beauty to take in. The road is lined with beautiful trees and plants, creating a peaceful and serene atmosphere for visitors to enjoy. Whether you're looking for a relaxing walk or simply want to immerse yourself in nature, The Long Walk Rd provides the perfect setting for an enjoyable outdoor experience.
name: The Long Walk Rd
address: Windsor, UK

detail_description: After exploring Windsor Castle, take some time to visit the Eton College Natural History Museum. This museum, which opened in 1875, offers a fascinating collection of specimens including bird eggs, fossils, and insects displayed in glass cabinets. The museum is open to the public on Sunday afternoons and provides an immersive experience for nature enthusiasts with its diverse range of exhibits showcasing the beauty and diversity of the natural world.
name: Eton College Natural History Museum
address: S Meadow Ln, Windsor, SL4 6ES, United Kingdom

detail_description: Windsor & Eton Riverside Station is the starting point for a delightful journey that includes must-see attractions like Windsor Castle, The Long Walk, and Windsor Great Park. A short walk from the station leads to the picturesque riverside where visitors can enjoy the serene beauty of swans and ducks. The station's charming location offers glimpses of the castle and a chance to witness the queen's presence when her flag is raised.
name: Windsor & Eton Riverside
address: Windsor, SL4 1NA, United Kingdom

excerpt: This modern restaurant with gilded-mirrors serves classic Moroccan and Mediterranean cuisine.
detail_description: Meimo is a modern restaurant adorned with gilded mirrors, offering classic Moroccan and Mediterranean cuisine. Visitors praise the authentic food and ambiance, making it a fantastic spot for a taste of Morocco. The family-owned establishment provides friendly service and a lovely atmosphere, perfect for enjoying mint tea or a full meal. Located near the castle, Meimo is known as one of Windsor's finest restaurants, where guests can savor delicious dishes in a welcoming setting.
name: Meimo
address: 69-70 Peascod St, Windsor, SL4 1DE, United Kingdom

excerpt: Compact pub outside Windsor Castle and Great Park with local beers, food and outdoor seating.
detail_description: The Two Brewers is a charming 18th-century pub located near Windsor Castle and Great Park. Its picturesque floral exterior and cozy interior make it a favorite among locals and visitors. The pub offers a selection of local beers, including options from Cornwall, along with classic pub food such as fish and chips. With limited indoor seating but ample outdoor picnic tables, it's an ideal place to enjoy post-stroll pints or socialize with friends in the lively atmosphere.
name: The Two Brewers
address: 34 Park St, Windsor, SL4 1LB, United Kingdom

detail_description: Windsor Royal Shopping Centre is located within a charming Victorian Grade II listed railway station, offering visitors a delightful shopping experience. The center features a replica steam locomotive called The Queen as its centerpiece, adding to the unique and historical ambiance of the space. It's an ideal destination for leisurely browsing and indulging in retail therapy.
name: Windsor Royal Shopping Centre
address: Arch 5 Goswell Hill, Windsor, SL4 1RH, UK

detail_description: When you arrive in Windsor, your journey will likely begin at the quaint Windsor & Eton Riverside station, which may seem understated given the town's royal heritage. However, for those seeking a touch of grandeur, Windsor Royal Station is just a stone's throw away from the other train hub, Windsor & Eton Central. This stunning structure has been transformed into a beautiful shopping center that perfectly complements its regal surroundings.
name: Windsor Royal Station
address: Jubilee Arch, Windsor, SL4 1PJ, UK

detail_description: Alexandra Gardens is a serene and picturesque park located in Windsor Great Park. It offers a perfect setting for relaxation, whether you're enjoying an iced coffee or taking a leisurely walk. The park provides stunning views of Windsor Castle, making it an ideal spot for capturing memorable photos. Many visitors have found solace in the early morning walks here during lockdown, appreciating the tranquil atmosphere and scenic beauty.
name: Alexandra Gardens
address: Windsor, UK

excerpt: Part of a larger complex owned by Eton College, this lake is an Olympic rowing training ground.
detail_description: Dorney Lake, located in Buckinghamshire, is a purpose-built rowing lake and an Olympic training ground. It was the rowing venue for the 2012 London Olympics. The area offers a traffic-free National Cycle Network trail and the Thames Path, making it ideal for walking or cycling. During spring and summer, public access is restricted, but from September to March, the lake reopens for leisure activities. Visitors can enjoy walking their dogs on a lead during this time.
name: Dorney Lake
address: Windsor, UK

detail_description: High St, located just across the river from Windsor, is a short walk from the town and offers a delightful shopping experience. The street is lined with charming independent stores, making it a perfect spot for leisurely strolls and browsing. If you're a fan of shopping, High St in Eton should definitely be on your list of things to do in Windsor.
name: High St
address: Windsor, UK

excerpt: A variety of shops & cafes compose this elegant shopping arcade in an 1850s rail station.
detail_description: Windsor Royal is an elegant shopping arcade located in the Windsor & Eton Central train station, which is connected to the Windsor & Eton Riverside station. The arcade features a variety of shops and cafes, offering a unique shopping and dining experience. Visitors can explore 40 boutique stores and casual cafes within the partially-covered old train station, which dates back to the mid-1800s.
name: Windsor Royal
address: 5 Goswell Hill, Windsor, SL4 1RH, United Kingdom

detail_description: Bachelor's Acre in Windsor is a charming park known for its whimsical statue of Queen Elizabeth II and her corgis, called The Windsor Lady. This simple yet lovely playground features an interactive water feature and play equipment for children. While there is limited shade, the green area is perfect for picnics on sunny days. Visitors can also find a clean public toilet within the park.
name: Bachelor’s Acre
address: 9 Bachelors Acre, Windsor, SL4 1ER, United Kingdom

excerpt: Classic pub featuring wine boxes on the walls, signed celebrity pictures and a British menu.
name: The Queen Victoria
address: 72 Peascod St, Windsor, SL4 1DE, United Kingdom

name: Museum of Eton Life
address: Brewhouse Yard, Baldwin's Shore, Windsor SL4 6DL, United Kingdom

excerpt: Historic riverside pub featuring an extensive drink menu & locally sourced homestyle cuisine.
detail_description: The Boatman is a historic riverside pub in Windsor, offering an extensive drink menu and locally sourced homestyle cuisine. It is the only proper pub by the river in Windsor, featuring spacious outdoor and all-weather terrace areas. Dogs are welcome both outside on the terrace and inside the bar. The menu offers a mix of traditional British favorites like fish and chips, sausage and mash, as well as Mediterranean dishes and delectable desserts.
name: The Boatman
address: 10 Thames Side, Windsor, SL4 1QN, United Kingdom

excerpt: Modern chain bar serving beer, cocktails, wine & sharing plates to an after-work crowd.
detail_description: All Bar One Windsor is a modern chain bar located in Windsor Royal Station, offering a stylish space for socializing with friends over drinks and sharing plates. Known for its high-quality food and diverse drink menu, it's a popular choice for after-work gatherings or catching up with friends. The venue also offers special events like Mother's Day bottomless brunches. Situated near the Royal Shopping Center, it provides a convenient spot to relax after shopping at the nearby boutiques.
name: All Bar One Windsor
address: 40a, Windsor Royal Station, Windsor SL4 1PJ, United Kingdom

detail_description: Reviewers have mentioned that it was their first visit to this eatery, and they were pleasantly surprised by its appearance from the road, which didn't do justice to the restaurant. The food at Gurkha Royale Restaurant & Bar was described as exceptional and presented nicely. The staff members were friendly, polite, and relaxed. Additionally, the facilities were impeccably clean, including the toilets. It's evident that the owners have made significant investments in the establishment, resulting in an impressive dining experience.
name: Gurkha Royale Restaurant & Bar
address: 85 Clewer Hill Rd, Windsor, SL4 4DE, United Kingdom

detail_description: Fudge Kitchen Ltd is a must-visit spot on Thames Street in Windsor. The shop offers a wide variety of fudge flavors, from salted caramel to maple walnut, all made on-site. Visitors can watch the fudge being made and interact with the enthusiastic staff. Customers praise the delicious and indulgent fudge, which they describe as soft and mouthwatering. The generous sampling policy allows visitors to taste the different flavors before making a selection.
name: Fudge Kitchen Ltd
address: 20 Thames St, Windsor, SL4 1PL, United Kingdom

detail_description: Windsor & Eton Central is a historic train station that used to be the terminus of the District line, offering Underground service from Mansion House in London to Windsor. While it now operates a shuttle service to Slough, most of its buildings have been transformed into chain restaurants and shops. The station is home to a full-sized replica GWR Achilles Class 4-2-2 Locomotive on display at Windsor Royal Shopping, an open-air arcade opposite Windsor Castle.
name: Windsor & Eton Central
address: Windsor, SL4 1PJ, United Kingdom

excerpt: Riverside park completed in 1902 with a military bandstand, mini golf & small amusement park.
detail_description: Alexandra Gardens is a picturesque riverside park completed in 1902, offering a variety of attractions and activities for visitors. It features a military bandstand, mini golf course, and a small amusement park, making it an ideal destination for families. The park's location along the Thames path provides stunning views of the river, boats, marina, and Brocas Meadows. Additionally, visitors can enjoy panoramic vistas of Windsor Castle and the Thames Valley while strolling through the gardens.
name: Alexandra Gardens
address: 3 Alma Rd, Windsor, SL4 3HU, United Kingdom

excerpt: Creative Modern European cuisine served in the smart restaurant of a riverside hotel and spa.
detail_description: The Brasserie at Sir Christopher Wren is a contemporary European eatery situated in a sophisticated riverside hotel and spa. They offer an innovative menu that showcases their culinary creativity. Customers can enjoy their meals in a stylish restaurant with picturesque views of the river. The afternoon tea set for two is particularly popular, featuring delectable sandwiches, warm scones, and delightful petit fours. Guests can also indulge in free-flowing tea and coffee.
name: The Brasserie at Sir Christopher Wren
address: 52-56 Thames St, Windsor, SL4 1PX, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Heartlake City Shopping Mall has received a 5-star rating due to its captivating name. It is not just a shopping destination, but a potential inspiration for a blues song. Despite the pleasant atmosphere of the mall and its likeness to other places, it has unfortunately been adversely affected by the C-19 virus like many other establishments. Nevertheless, there is hope for recovery and rebuilding their businesses.
name: Heartlake City Shopping Mall
address: Winkfield Rd, Windsor, SL4 4AY, United Kingdom

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Windsor, The Ivy Windsor is a charming new establishment that has quickly captured the hearts of locals and visitors alike. Just a stone's throw from the iconic Windsor Castle, this restaurant boasts an inviting red brick exterior that reflects its historic surroundings. Inside, guests can enjoy a variety of intimate dining areas adorned with vibrant decor and quirky touches typical of The Ivy group.
name: The Ivy Windsor
address: 31 High St, Windsor, SL4 1PQ, United Kingdom

detail_description: Bray Cured is a must-visit for food enthusiasts in Windsor. This delectable street food market takes place every third weekend of the month, offering an array of mouthwatering culinary delights. If you happen to be in town when the market is open, make sure not to miss this delightful opportunity to savor some local flavors and indulge in a vibrant foodie experience.
name: Bray Cured (at Windsor Independent Market)
address: Independent Market, Peascod St, Windsor SL4 1DN, United Kingdom

name: YourParkingSpace Oscar Lodge Windsor Car Park
address: 65 Vansittart Rd, Windsor, SL4 5DB, United Kingdom

excerpt: 4,800 acres of park managed by The Crown Estate with a lake and waterfall, plus visitor centres.
detail_description: Windsor Great Park, managed by The Crown Estate, spans 4,800 acres and boasts a rich royal history dating back over 1,000 years. Visitors can explore historical monuments, ancient forests, and beautiful horticultural displays while encountering rare wildlife and plants. The park features the famous Long Walk, a 2.5-mile path from Windsor Castle to the Copper Horse statue of King George III.
name: Windsor Great Park
address: The Crown Estate Windsor Great Park, SL4 2HT, United Kingdom

excerpt: Miniature toy palace designed by Lutyens, with detailed furniture, working lifts and running water.
detail_description: Queen Mary's Dolls' House is a remarkable miniature palace located in Windsor Castle. It was designed by Sir Edwin Lutyens and presented to Queen Mary in 1924. The house is filled with intricate details, including working lifts, running water from tiny faucets, and monogrammed linens. The craftsmanship of the miniatures created by leading artists and designers of the time is truly impressive.
name: Queen Mary's Dolls' House
address: Windsor Castle, Windsor, SL4 1NJ, United Kingdom

excerpt: Nursery and shop with a casual cafe offering area-sourced food from breakfast to afternoon tea.
detail_description: Crocus at Dorney Court is a charming nursery and shop with a relaxed café that serves locally-sourced meals from morning to afternoon. The café offers an extensive menu featuring breakfast, lunch, and delectable cake options. Visitors can enjoy the stunning walled garden and are welcome to bring leashed dogs. The friendly staff provides excellent service, making it a popular spot for walkers and cyclists, especially with its proximity to Dorney Lake.
name: Crocus at Dorney Court
address: Court Ln, Dorney, Windsor SL4 6QP, United Kingdom

detail_description: Located in Egham, England, the John F Kennedy Memorial is a must-visit site near the Runnymede National Trust. The memorial features an artwork called "The Jurors," consisting of 12 bronze chairs symbolizing clause 39 of the Magna Carta. Visitors can take a leisurely walk around this open-air art installation and explore the detailed summary of each chair on the national trust website.
name: John F Kennedy Memorial
address: Englefield Green, Egham, TW20 0YU, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Diamond Jubilee Water Fountains, located near Windsor Castle, were commissioned in 2012 to celebrate the Queen's Diamond Jubilee. The fountains are well-maintained and offer a beautiful sight during both day and night when illuminated. The surrounding grounds provide a lovely place for a leisurely walk with scenic views. Despite occasional closures, it is highly recommended to visit this small but posh park with its carefully considered landscaping and timed water flow sequences.
name: Diamond Jubilee Water Fountains
address: Goswell Rd, Windsor, SL4 1QX, United Kingdom

excerpt: Memorial statue cast in bronze honoring fallen Irish guardsmen.
detail_description: The Soldier's Statue, also known as the Irish Guardsman Statue, is a six-foot bronze monument located in Windsor high street. The statue stands on a plinth made from bronze salvaged from the Iraq war and was commissioned by the Irish Guards. It is particularly noteworthy that the metal used for this military memorial was brought back from Iraq and melted down to create this poignant tribute to fallen guardsmen.
name: Soldier's Statue
address: 3 St Alban's St, Windsor, SL4 1PF, United Kingdom

detail_description: Downtown Windsor boasts several renowned landmarks, including the King George V Memorial and Alexandra Gardens. For brief outings in the area, Savill Garden serves as a splendid choice. Additionally, popular attractions such as Windsor Castle and Eton College are not to be missed. Despite its considerable distance, this sculpture is well worth the effort, particularly on a delightful day. The memorial impresses with its appealing water feature and modest scale.
name: King George V Memorial
address: Windsor, SL4 1RQ, United Kingdom

excerpt: This large meadow along the Thames River offers picnicking with views of Windsor Castle.
detail_description: The expansive field beside the Thames River provides an opportunity for outdoor dining while enjoying glimpses of Windsor Castle.
name: The Brocas
address: F9PP+JM, Windsor, UK
